This paper deals with the problem of providing incentives to users in a mobile edge computing system, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also uses game theory to model the behavior of self-interested users, which is a common approach in the subfield of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper considers the security risks associated with D2D computing, which is a topic in the subfield of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also uses epidemic models to analyze the spread of DDoS attacks, which is a common approach in the subfield of complex systems and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a contract-based incentive mechanism, which is a topic in the subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC).
